# ALX Code of Conduct

## Introduction

ALX Africa's SE Program strives to provide a safe and inclusive learning environment for all learners, free from harassment, prejudice, discrimination, and intellectual property violations.

## Mission of ALX Africa

We aim to transform Africa by developing 3 million ethical and entrepreneurial leaders by 2035. Our Software Engineering Program focuses on equipping the next generation of software engineers with the foundational skills and practical experience needed to thrive in the tech industry.

## Our Pledge

We are committed to fostering an open, welcoming, diverse, inclusive, and healthy community. We pledge to act and interact in ways that contribute to a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of their background or identity.

## Our Values

* Courage
* Humility
* Adventure
* Initiative
* Resilience

## Copyright

Plagiarism of program content, including copying code for project submissions, is strictly prohibited and considered a severe offense. We encourage collaboration and learning from others but emphasize the importance of producing original work that demonstrates your understanding and skills.
